title: For Sale:  HK SP89 German PreBan 9mm Pistol KA date code (1990) w/ Extras
postcontent: Very low rd count. Xtras include an attache padded soft case (worth $125) that carries the pistol and mags/accessories, the factory HK rear-mounted nylon single-point sling ($75), 3 magazines ($150), and factory original instruction manual. All parts on it are 100% original German HK date stamped. I bought it from an older gentleman who purchased it brand new in 1990 and only fired a couple mags thru it and then put it in his safe for the last 26 years until I bought it last year. Since I acquired it, the pistol's remained in my safe and I've never fired a single round out of it, as I have several MP5-type firearms and don't have much time to make it out to the range with my hectic work schedule. When he shipped it to me, he put the mags in the same case as the pistol so there are some minor wear marks (none of which go down to bare meteal) on the right side of the receiver. Other than that, its a really clean pistol, especially for its age, and as evident by the minimal bolt carrier wear, and has seen very little use in the last 27 years.  I got a quote from TPM Outfitters out of Carrollton, TX to completely strip and refinish it for $175 if you wanted a perfect and pristine SP89. TPM built a HK94 and MP5K clone that I bought and they do absolutely flawless work and have a finish that looks better and is more durable than the factory HK finish. With it being refinished and flawless, and the very low round count, this pistol would be worth $5000-5500 all day long, as I've seen them sell in that range over the last couple years. These gems only continue to go up in value, especially in pristine condition, as they were only imported in limited numbers between 1989 and 1994 and many remain in private collections never to be seen again. But if you're someone who isn't so particular about having a pristine safe queen and just enjoys taking your firearms out to the range or throwing it in the nightstand as the ultimate Personal Defense Weapon in your home, it would be perfect for that as-is. Paid $5000, my loss is your gain.Also have a LNIB original OEM HK Pulse Beam Model 100 Laser Sight available that fits the SP89, MP5, HK33, HK53, G3, HK94, HK93, and HK91 rifles and pistols.WARNING! Don't be fooled by other low priced listings on Armslist or elsewhere for genuine SP89s for $2500-$3000. THESE ARE SCAMS! Over the last 5 years I have not seen a single genuine German SP89 go for under $3500-$4000 and those had a tons of rounds thru them and were beat to hell. Most in good to NIB range from $4500-$6500. Don't fall victim to these scam artists that are unregistered with Armslist, they will only take your money. Willing to accept credit card payment thru discreet Paypal transaction with buyer to cover any PP fees. Private sale, no FFL fees or paperwork to hassle with. If a face to face meet isn't possible, shipping is $65 via FedEx Overnight. postcontent: The Thompson was one of the earliest submachine guns to incorporate a double-column, double-feed box magazine design, which undoubtedly contributed to the gun's reputation for reliability. In addition, the gun performed better than most after exposure to rain, dirt, and mud.The selective-fire (semi- or fully automatic) Thompson fires from the "open bolt" position, in which the bolt is held fully to rearward by the sear when cocked. When the trigger is depressed, the bolt is released, traveling forward to chamber and simultaneously fire the first and subsequent rounds until either the trigger is released or the ammunition is exhausted.
